Ricky Ponting to Stand Down as Australia Cricket Captain, Telegraph Says

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-03-28T22:39:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/ricky-ponting-to-stand-down-as-australia-cricket-captain-telegraph-says.html
Ricky Ponting  is set to announce
today that he will stand down as captain of  Australia ’s cricket
team, the  Daily Telegraph  reported, without saying where it got
the information.   Ponting, 36, will remain as a batsman in the team and vice-
captain  Michael Clarke  is expected to take over as skipper, the
newspaper said.  A senior Australian cricketer will make a “major
announcement” at the Sydney Cricket Ground at 1 p.m. local time
today, Cricket Australia spokesman Philip Pope said in a
telephone interview.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  